The paper discusses the use of cryo-electron microscopy (EM) for determining the 3-D structure of macromolecules, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of algorithms for analyzing multiple classes of molecules mixed together, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MM) and data analysis (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for reconstructing higher dimensional objects, which could be relevant to scientific computing (cs.SI).
